base:age_70 a type:Date ;
    rdfs:label "age 70" ;
    prop:extractedFrom """The risk of septic shock increases at age 60, with those at age 70 having the highest risk of dying from sepsis.[11]
The mortality rate from sepsis, especially if it is not treated rapidly with the needed medications in a hospital, is approximately 40% in adults and 25% in children.[68][69]""" ;
