base:norepinephrine a type:Treatment ;
    rdfs:label "norepinephrine" ;
    prop:extractedFrom "If the placement of a central venous catheter is delayed then norepinephrine can be given through a peripheral IV.[59]",
        "Norepinephrine is often used as a first-line treatment for hypotensive septic shock because evidence shows that there is a relative deficiency of vasopressin when shock continues for 24 to 48 hours.[77] Norepinephrine raises blood pressure through a vasoconstriction effect, with little effect on stroke volume and heart rate.[5]" ;
