    prop:administer_after base:sepsis ;
    prop:extractedFrom "At one point it was recommended that antibiotics be administered one hour after initial recognition of sepsis.[1]",
        "Empiric antibiotics should be narrowed, preferably to a single antibiotic, once the blood culture returns with a particular bacteria that has been isolated.[47",
        "In severe sepsis and septic shock, broad-spectrum antibiotics (usually two, a β-lactam antibiotic with broad coverage, or broad-spectrum carbapenem combined with fluoroquinolones, macrolides, or aminoglycosides) are recommended.",
        "Intraventricular antibiotics used included colistin, vancomycin, tigecycline, and amikacin." ;
